29:["$","p","p-18",{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"className":"text-foreground font-semibold","children":"Staking in a bear market:"}]," You earn 3% on an asset that's dropping 50%. Net result: massive loss. Staking amplifies bear market pain because your capital is locked in a depreciating asset with a tiny yield cushion."]}]
2a:["$","p","p-19",{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"className":"text-foreground font-semibold","children":"Funding rate arbitrage in a bear market:"}]," Volatility increases, which typically increases rate dispersion across exchanges. Cross-exchange spreads often widen in panics because different venues respond to selling pressure at different speeds. Zirodelta's engine profits from dispersion, not direction."]}]
2b:["$","p","p-20",{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"className":"text-foreground font-semibold","children":"Winner: Funding rate arbitrage."}]," Bear markets are where the strategy difference is sharpest. Staking yields don't compensate for price drawdowns. Arbitrage spreads tend to widen."]}]
