2d:["$","p","p-21",{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"className":"text-foreground font-semibold","children":"Staking:"}]," Deposit tokens, pick a validator or liquid staking protocol, wait. Maybe 10 minutes of effort. Liquid staking (stETH, mSOL) is essentially one click."]}]
2e:["$","p","p-22",{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"className":"text-foreground font-semibold","children":"Funding rate arbitrage (manual):"}]," Monitor rates across exchanges, fund multiple accounts, execute hedges, manage margin, close and rotate. Full-time job for a human."]}]
2f:["$","p","p-23",{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"className":"text-foreground font-semibold","children":"Funding rate arbitrage (via Zirodelta):"}]," Deposit $ZDLT as collateral → protocol handles everything. The Beta-X1 engine scans rates every 15 minutes across 19+ exchanges, executes hedges autonomously, distributes yield per 8-hour epoch in USDT. Still more complex than clicking \"stake\" on Lido, but the execution is autonomous."]}]
30:["$","p","p-24",{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"className":"text-foreground font-semibold","children":"Winner: Staking"}]," on simplicity. Zirodelta closes the gap with automation, but staking is fundamentally simpler."]}]
